annotationA: Selenide, water dikinase is a selenophosphate synthetase (SPS) that catalyzes the synthesis of selenophosphate from selenide, ATP, and water, producing AMP and inorganic phosphate as products. SPS are well conserved proteins involved in selenium metabolism; Belongs to the selenophosphate synthase 1 family. Class II subfamily
annotationB: O-phosphoseryl-tRNA(Sec) selenium transferase; Converts O-phosphoseryl-tRNA(Sec) to selenocysteinyl- tRNA(Sec) required for selenoprotein biosynthesis
